This is one of the busiest #CornerBakeryCafe I have been to. Tried it during a Big Bus Tour of Chicago with my dad who was visiting for which they provide a coupon. As tourist attractions are nearby and tour bus drop offs are nearby, this place is packed with tourists inside and outside where they have seatings which is nice in the summer. There is a long line to order, but they do have three staff so that is good. As a tourist you require two things bathroom breaks and fully charged phone (at least not low battery) - bathroom trips will take longer than to order as they have longer line and one stall. You have few power sockets not close to the tables, so you just got to find the right spot to sit and know to balance your phone (which is what I did). No complaints about the food or staff - GOOD FOOD & EFFICIENT STAFF - HOW ELSE DO YOU HAVE A HUGE CROWD AND STILL MANAGE THEM. LOVE CORNER BAKERY. When staying in the nearby Hotel Chicago Downtown we found the Corner Bakery Cafe when looking for a good breakfast venue on our first morning in Chicago.  While it is a busy cafe we found the atmosphere, food, prices and friendly and helpful staff so much to our taste that we made it our breakfast venue for the remainder of our stay in Chicago.  It is located on the ground floor of the London Exchequer Building at DuSable Bridge on the junction of East Wacker Drive and Michigan Avenue. The Corner Bakery Cafe is closed temporarily at present for refurbishment and I hope they will do so successfully as it would be a pity to lose the old world atmosphere coupled with modern efficiency which we experienced there

It was topped with bacon,scallions and cheddar cheese. The soup had chunks of potato and cheese throughout it was perfect. My  sandwich was delish. We also snuck in a cinnamon roll, they were nice enough to warm it up for us as well....All that gooeyness did not disappoint!
